# WHERE vs HAVING
==================


WHERE                          vs                 HAVING
filter rows                                  filter groups

applied before group by                      applied after group by

use where clause if condition                 use where clause if condition
doesn't contain group by                      doesn't contain group by

Note:-
-----
If condition contain group function use having clause,if condition not having group function use where clause


Q)Dept wise total salary where dept no=1,2

Ans) select emp_department_number as department , sum(emp_salary) from employee
     where emp_department_number in(1,2) group by emp_department_number order by 1 asc;


Flow:-
from employee it will fetch all records or 1,2 departements,then it will group by department then it will ordered by department number.

Note:-
-------
 Group functions are not allowed in Where clause ,group functions innosense min,max,avg,sum.These are allowed in select and having only.

Below query will not work
-------------------------
select emp_department_number as department , sum(emp_salary) from employee
     where emp_department_number in(1,2) and sum(emp_salary)>10000 group by emp_department_number order by 1 asc;

Q)dept wise total salaries where dept no=1,2 and sum(sal)>10000

